<item>
            <title>[LU-16716] add test to verify irreparable OI mapping</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16716</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;OI scrub is able to handle mapping in below cases:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;get inode or LMA xattr fail (return code is not -ENOENT, -ESTALE or -ENOMEM).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;FID provided by client is not seen in inode iteration, this happens when client get FID by readdir, but this FID doesn&apos;t point to any inode on disk.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;OI scrub found the correct mapping, but fails to update OI files.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Add tests for these cases to ensure they are always correctly handled. And the code of osd_fid_lookup() can be cleaned up to make it easier to understand and maintain.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
